 wie dem Selbstgespräch und der Dokumentation von Alltag, der Erinnerung, dem Bezeugen von Leid und Verfolgung sowie einer steten Selbstkonstruktion. Untersucht werden Tagebücher bekannter wie unbekannter Frauen – von Rosa Mayreder über Elise Richter bis hin zu einer Müllerin namens Theresia Vogt.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aDiariesxHistory and criticism. 0aFeminismxHistory. 0aNational socialism and women. 0aWomen and wary20th centuryxHistory. 0aWomenzAustriaxHistoryy20th century. 0aWomenzAustriaxSocial conditionsy20th century. 0aWomenzGermanyy20th centuryvDiaries. 7aHISTORY / Modern / 20th Century.2bisacsh1 aBrommer, Ingrid, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDusini, Arno, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGerhalter, Li, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGerhalter, Li, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHelfert, Veronika, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHämmerle, Christa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHämmerle, Christa, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKarner, Christine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMöckel, Benjamin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchwarz, Ulrich, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSemanek, Brigitte, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSteele, Helen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2016z9783110485103oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2016z9783110485189